{| class="wikitable" style="margin: 0.5em auto; clear: both; font-size:95%"
|- style="text-align: center;"

<noinclude>
----
==Templates Discussed on this Page==
This template is to be used in coordination with the following:
::[[Template:s-start]] or [[Template:start succession box]]
::[[Template:s-bef]] or [[Template:succession before]]
::[[Template:s-aft]] or [[Template:succession after]]
::[[Template:s-ttl]] or [[Template:succession title]]
::[[Template:end]] or [[Template:end box]]
::[[Template:s-non]]
::[[Template:s-new]]
::[[Template:s-inc]]
::[[Template:s-reg]]

==Instructions for Use==
To use, follow these instructions:<br/>
:Enter the start field so the program recognizes the table<br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-start}}</nowiki><br/>
:Enter the name of the predecessor<br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-bef|before=[['''Enter Predecessor here''']]}}</nowiki><br/>
:Enter the title of the person on whose page you are working.<br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|title=[['''Enter Title here''']]</nowiki>
:Also, enter the years during which they held that title.<br/>
::<nowiki>|years=[['''Enter start date here''']]-[['''Enter end date here''']]}}</nowiki><br/>
:Enter the name of the successor:<br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-aft|after=[['''Enter Successor here''']]}}</nowiki><br/>
:If they held additional titles after, place the following and repeat as necessary:<br/>
::<nowiki>|-</nowiki><br/>
:Once everything is done, type:<br/>
::<nowiki>{{end}}</nowiki><br/>

===S-start, s-bef, s-ttl, s-aft, end===
That is how to do the most simple one.  When it is done, it will look like this:<br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-start}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-bef|before=[['''Enter Predecessor here''']]}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|title=[['''Enter Title here''']]</nowiki>
::<nowiki>|years=[['''Enter start date here''']]-[['''Enter end date here''']]}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-aft|after=[['''Enter Successor here''']]}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{end}}</nowiki><br/>

Which will look something like this:
{{s-start}}
{{s-bef|before=Martin}}
{{s-ttl|title=King of Europe|years=1492-1528}}
{{s-aft|after=Robert}}
{{end}}

===Rows===
A row marker can be created in nearly all the templates immediately following the "'''s-'''" field.  They help designate if someone gained a position in office from another person, or lost a position while in office, as well as other more complex scenarios.

In most fields, simply type:
::<nowiki>{{s-EXTENSION OF TEMPLATE HERE|</nowiki>'''row=INSERT ROWS HERE'''<nowiki>|REMAINDER OF FORM}}</nowiki>

The number corresponds to the number of rows this name or title overlaps in regard to the other rows.  Lists of title-holders are usually in order of the granting of the title, beginning with the oldest titles held.  

Remember also to place:
<nowiki>|-</nowiki>
between every row on the list.  This text is already imbedded into the Template:s-aft, Template:s-non, and Template:s-inc, but if you are ending with a different template, place these characters or the computer will not recognize a new row.  It is used in the following example only to demonstrate its purpose.

An example of the code is as follows:

::<nowiki>{{s-start}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-bef|rows=1|before=Andrew}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|title=King of Australia</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>|years=1620-1675}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-aft|rows=2|after=Christian}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>|-</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-bef|rows=1|before=Willem}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|rows=1|title=King of Oceana</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>|years=1631–1675}}</nowiki><br/>
::<nowiki>{{end}}</nowiki><br/>

When complete, this form appears as thus:
{{s-start}}
{{s-bef|rows=1|before=Andrew}}
{{s-ttl|title=King of Australia
|years=1620-1675}}
{{s-aft|rows=2|after=Christian}}
|-
{{s-bef|rows=1|before=Willem}}
{{s-ttl|rows=1|title=King of Oceana
|years=1620–1675}}
{{end}}

===S-non===
To create a table for someone whose title expires, went extinct, or otherwise went into disuse upon their death, use the following:

Template:s-non (with others)
::<nowiki>{{s-start}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-bef|before=INSERT PREDECESSOR HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|title=TITLE OF PERSON|years=INSERT YEAR HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-non|reason=GIVE BRIEF REASON WHY NO MORE TITLE (eg. Extinct)}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{end}}</nowiki>

Which looks like:
{{s-start}}
{{s-bef|before=Chinggis}}
{{s-ttl|title=King of Asia|years=1263-1320}}
{{s-non|reason=Conquest by <br/>Arabian Empire}}
{{end}}

===S-new===
To create a table that begins with a newly created title, use this:

Template:s-new (with others)
::<nowiki>{{s-start}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-new}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|title=TITLE OF PERSON|years=INSERT YEARS HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-aft|after=INSERT PREDECESSOR HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{end}}</nowiki>

Which looks like:
{{s-start}}
{{s-new}}
{{s-ttl|title=King of Africa|years=1820-1830}}
{{s-aft|after=Amal}}
{{end}}

===S-inc===
To create a table for someone who is the incumbant (current title holder), use the following:

Template:s-non (with others)
::<nowiki>{{s-start}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-bef|before=INSERT PREDECESSOR HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|title=TITLE OF PERSON|years=INSERT FIRST YEAR FOLLOWED BY "–present"}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-inc}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{end}}</nowiki>

Which looks like:
{{s-start}}
{{s-bef|before=George}}
{{s-ttl|title=King of North America|years=2001-present}}
{{s-inc}}
{{end}}

===S-reg===
To create a table for someone ruled with the aide of another (regent, coruler, &c.), use the following: (Note: This form has no "rows" option.)

Template:s-reg (with others)
::<nowiki>{{s-start}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-bef|before=INSERT PREDECESSOR HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-ttl|title=TITLE OF PERSON|years=INSERT YEARS HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-reg|regent=TITLE OF REGENT|years=INSERT YEARS HERE}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{s-aft|after=INSERT SUCCESSOR HERE)}}</nowiki>
::<nowiki>{{end}}</nowiki>

Which looks like:
{{s-start}}
{{s-bef|before=Philip}}
{{s-ttl|title=Queen of Antarctica|years=1889-1914}}
{{s-reg|regent=Philip|years=1889-1897}}
{{s-aft|after=Margaret}}
{{end}}

==Chart noting all of these tables combined==
Using the rows feature of the templates, very advanced tables can be created to help in situations with people who hold many posts, especially [[British Prime Minister]]s.  The following is a hypothetical chart with at least one use of all the forms above:

{{s-start}}

{{s-new}}
{{s-ttl|title=Queen of India|years=1972–1983}}
{{s-reg|regent=Michael|years=1972-1975}}
{{s-aft|rows=2|after=Arnold}}
{{s-bef|rows=3|before=Elizabeth}}
{{s-ttl|title=Lady High of Oceana|years=1975-1983}}
|-
{{s-ttl|title=Empress of Arabia|years=1975-1993}}
{{s-non|reason=Title merged with<br/>Great Khanna of Asia}}
{{s-ttl|title=Grand Duchess of Europa|years=1975–1999}}
{{s-aft|rows=2|after=Felicia}}
{{s-bef|rows=2|before=Karl}}
{{s-ttl|title=Chief Sultana of Africa|years=1993-1999}}
|-
{{s-ttl|title=Great Khanna of Asia|years=1993–present}}
{{s-inc|rows=2}}
{{s-bef|before=Diane}}
{{s-ttl|title=Honrary Queen of Australia|years=2003–present}}
{{end}}
</noinclude>

{| class="wikitable" style="margin: 0.5em auto; clear: both; font-size:95%"
|- style="text-align: center;"

